Meeting of Frontrunners of Songun Revolution Opens 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 5 (KCNA) -- A meeting of frontrunners of the Songun revolution was opened at the April 25 House of Culture in Pyongyang Monday.
 Present there were senior party, army and state officials, Cabinet members, officials of the party, armed forces and power organs, working people's organizations, ministries and national institutions, servicepersons and frontrunners in the fields of economy, science, education, literature and art, sports, public health and media. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A congratulatory message of the Central Committee and the Central Military Commission of the Workers' Party of Korea to the participants in the meeting was read out there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The message said that the DPRK's access to nuclear deterrent was an epoch-making event in the history of the Korean nation as it provided a sure guarantee for putting an end to outsiders' aggression and interference and bringing eternal prosperity to the country. It was also the most shining victory won in the tempest of the Songun revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the last two years our army and people have made successes greater than what was done in the past several years in the economic construction and thus put the national economy as a whole on an orbit of steady upswing, the message noted, and said: The Central Committee and the Central Military Commission of the WPK highly praise all the officers and men of the Korean People's Army and the people for having worked hard to strikingly display the might of Songun Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Choe Thae Bok, alternate member of the Political Bureau and secretary of the WPK Central Committee, delivered a report at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter said that the Korean revolution, which was pioneered and emerged victorious with the help of arms under the banner of the Juche idea, has greeted the golden days of its development under the Songun politics of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is the most admirable success made in the general march for the Songun revolution, he said, is that the biggest efforts were channeled into increasing the nation's military capabilities for self-defence, thus making it possible for the DPRK to demonstrate its might as a socialist military power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to the successful nuclear test the DPRK conducted with its own efforts and technology on the threshold of the significant anniversary of the WPK last year, he said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This helped the DPRK secure a reliable military guarantee for its prosperity and, as a full-fledged nuclear weapons state, greatly contribute to defending global peace and security. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today the DPRK has the invincible revolutionary army and powerful war deterrent. So we can declare confidently with high pride that we carried out all what should be done to defend ourselves and Songun Korea has become secure for all ages. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK has taken the steadfast position of a power in political and ideological and military aspects. At last, an emotion-charged era of struggle has set in when our army and people should push ahead with the building of a socialist economic power after definitely rounding off the "Arduous March" and the forced march. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Now is the time for them to unite as one in mind under the banner of Songun, bring into full play the inexhaustible potentials they have built up in the do-or-die spirit and effect a great surge on all fronts of building a great prosperous and powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 "Let us make a general advance toward the peak of a great prosperous powerful nation, full of confidence and pride of being the victors of the Songun revolution!" This is the militant slogan that we should hold high. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  All the servicepersons and people should speed up the general march for the Songun revolution this year marking significant revolutionary holidays and thus eternally glorify the immortal revolutionary history and feats of President Kim Il Sung and fully display the invincibility of the Songun revolution advancing under the leadership of Kim Jong Il and the spirit of the powerful and prosperous country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We should value the single-minded unity, the greatest gain of the Korean revolution, and cement the unity of the entire party and army and all the people based on the revolutionary comradeship around the leader whenever the situation turns out to be tense and difficult tasks may face them in the revolution and construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is also imperative for us to more thoroughly arm ourselves with the great Juche idea, the Songun idea, firmly preserve its purity and steadily push forward the revolution and construction along the road of Songun guided by the Juche idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Underlining the need to keep directing big efforts into increasing the nation's military capabilities for self-defence with the KPA as a core, taking the Juche-based Songun idea and line as immutable guidelines of our Party and revolution, the reporter continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We should continue to give top priority to the development of the national defence industry, a material basis of the military capacity, with the transparent viewpoint that one can live without drops but not without bullets. And it is necessary to let all the people learn the military affairs with sincerity and turn the whole country into an impregnable fortress by making the spirit of attaching importance to the military affairs prevail over the whole society. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The main task facing us at present is to shore up the economy as early as possible and radically improve the standard of people's living by concentrating all possible efforts, the reporter said, and stressed: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We should demonstrate once again the spirit of the courageous army and people of the DPRK and the mettle of Songun Korea determined to find itself in the van of the world through the on-going gigantic advance for building an economic power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting continues.

Choe Thae Bok on DPRK's Contribution to Global Peace 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 5 (KCNA) -- As a full-fledged nuclear weapons state, the DPRK has become able to make a great contribution to protecting global peace and security.
 Choe Thae Bok, alternate Politburo member and secretary of the C.C., Workers' Party of Korea, stressed this in a report at the meeting of frontrunners of the Songun revolution which opened at the April 25 House of Culture on Monday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to the successful nuclear test conducted by the DPRK with its own efforts and technology last year, he said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today the DPRK has the invincible revolutionary army and powerful war deterrent. So we can declare confidently with high pride that we carried out all what should be done to defend ourselves and Songun Korea has become secure for all ages. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK has taken the steadfast position of a power in political and ideological and military aspects. At last, an emotion-charged era of struggle has set in when our army and people should push ahead with the building of a socialist economic power after definitely rounding off the "Arduous March" and the forced march, he added.

Oath-taking Meeting of Youths and Children in Mt. Paektu 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Samjiyon, February 4 (KCNA) -- A national oath-taking meeting of youths and children took place in front of the old home of Kim Jong Il in the secret camp of Mt. Paektu on Feb. 4 with the approach of his birthday.
 The participants in the meeting placed a floral basket and bouquets before the mosaic of the three generals of Mt. Paektu erected in the secret camp and made a deep bow to them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the call of Ri Myong Won, secretary of the C.C., the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League, the participants made oaths voicing the rock-firm faith and will of the 8 million youth and children to accomplish the long journey of Songun revolution started in Mt. Paektu under the leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They said the youth and children, the successors to the revolution, would resolutely defend and add brilliance to the glorious revolutionary traditions, the deep and stout roots and eternal foundation of the Korean revolution, which were established in the flames of the great anti-Japanese war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They said the young people would take the van of the struggle to safeguard the gains of the Songun revolution, keeping a tight hold on the Songun idea and line of Juche as the guideline, and fulfil their mission and role as the most viable fighting unit in accomplishing the cause of the Workers' Party of Korea.  They vowed to dash to such difficult toilsome work sites as the construction site of the Paektusan Songun Youth Power Station and become young heroes and patriotic youths of the Songun era in the drive for the building of an economic power with the mettle of Thaechon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the occasion of the 80th anniversary of the founding of the Young Communist League of Korea, they said, the young men and women will firmly defend and glorify the feats performed by President Kim Il Sung in the Korean youth movement and the tradition of the youth movement and firmly build up the youth league into a revolutionary organization with strong organizational ability and fighting efficiency. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They were briefed on the historic relics carefully preserved in the old home, while seeing them with keen interest.

Intensified Reunification Movement Urged 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 5 (KCNA) -- An inaugural meeting of the "Blue Response" of the Youth Cultural Center for Reunification was reportedly held in Seoul on Jan. 30.
 Present at the meeting were members of organizations of youth and students and civil and public organizations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Addressing the meeting, the chief director of the "Blue Response" said the words "blue response" implied a call upon the youth and students in the south and north of Korea to be united as one. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Congratulatory speeches were made by the permanent representative of the Youth and Students Headquarters of the South Side Committee for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers said the youth and students were the future of the nation and the heroes of the reunified country and expressed the hope that the organization would work energetically for peace and reunification in the future. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An inaugural declaration was read out at the meeting, which called for implementing the June 15 joint declaration and invigorating among the youth and students the movement for national reunification.

U.S. Imperialists Massively Deploy Arms and Stage Aerial War Exercise 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 5 (KCNA) -- The U.S. imperialists have swiftly deployed massive aggression forces in and around south Korea, getting more undisguised in their scheme to make a preemptive attack on the DPRK, according to military sources.
 They deployed a wing of F-117 Stealth fighter bombers and over 300 support personnel brought from the U.S. mainland in south Korea in January and brought formations of F-15 fighter bombers and F/A-18 pursuit and assault planes from overseas to their air force bases in south Korea in February. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These formations have launched into exercises of terrain familiarization, navigation flight and strike at land targets with Kunsan, Suwon, Kumi and Pusan areas as the operational theatre. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, on Feb. 1 and 2, over 250 F-16 fighter bombers and A-10 assault planes of the 7th Air Force of the U.S. imperialists in south Korea flew the skies over Kunsan, Ronsan, Chonan, Tangjin, Wonju, Ryechon and Phyongchang areas in their frantic exercises of air battle, close air support and strike at land target. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the other hand, the U.S. imperialists are busy with preparations for deploying F-22A Raptor Stealth fighter bombers in their Kadena air base, Okinawa of Japan, by Feb. 10, while planning to send the extra-large aircraft carrier Reagan to Yokosuka Port of Japan in addition to the carrier Kitty Hawk which is already there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Timing to coincide with this, Guam-based B-52s are making shuttle flights between the U.S. mainland and the island in their madcap long-distance flight exercise targeted at the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These noisy moves of the U.S. imperialist aggression forces suggest that they are rapidly going over to a practical stage from the stage of creating a crisis for a preemptive attack on the DPRK.

Arms Buildup Protested in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 5 (KCNA) -- The People for Achieving Peace and Reunification in south Korea reportedly held the 64th rally for peace and disarmament in front of the Defense Ministry building in Seoul on Jan. 30 and condemned the military authorities for arms buildup that incites a war crisis on the Korean Peninsula from the outset of this year.
 Speakers at the rally referred to the fact that at the beginning of the year the Defense Ministry, the Joint Chiefs of Staff Headquarters and the Office for Defense Affairs announced one after another plans on introduction and development of large-scale weapons system, including additional introduction of F-15Ks, establishment of the Missile Defense system, development of assaulting helicopters and introduction of unmanned reconnaissance planes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The military authorities are pushing the situation of the Korean Peninsula to the verge of war from the outset of the year by following the U.S. war policy, and such moves can never be allowed, they held. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They expressed the determination to vigorously struggle to get the above-said plans scrapped in solidarity with the peace-loving forces at home and abroad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A written protest was read out at the rally in denunciation of the Defense Ministry's scheme for armament. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the rally, the participants staged a street demonstration.

Songun Politics, Treasured Sword for Defense of Nation: Rodong Sinmun
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 5 (KCNA) -- Songun politics is a powerful treasured sword for defense of the nation which safeguards the dignity and sovereignty of the nation and protects the destiny of the whole nation, repulsing aggressive challenges of outside forces with the arms of justice, declares Rodong Sinmun Monday.
 Noting that the Songun politics of the DPRK is based on the historical lesson that the dignity and sovereignty of the country and the nation can be defended only with powerful military capacity, the author of the article goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Songun politics is one which firmly defends the dignity and sovereignty of the nation from the aggressive threats of foreign forces by building up the strongest military capacity, giving the top priority to the military affairs in the state affairs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If one is weak in strength today when the imperialist forces freely invade sovereign states and force bloodshed and death upon their people, one can find no hearer, however loudly he may cry for justice, but only suffer humiliation, maltreatment and insult. One can defend oneself, have proper say and be respected only when one is strong. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Now the gun sights of the U.S. imperialists for aggression are leveled at the Korean Peninsula. The U.S., however, dare not ignite a war, only snarling with its sword unsheathed. This is because it cannot see any military possibility of realizing its ambition of dominating Korea in view of the balance of forces on the peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The mysterious weapon of defense of peace which quelled the war hysterics of the U.S. imperialists, the warmongers, is the very Songun politics of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists dare not cross the doorstep of a Korean war, though they are thirsty for a war. The mighty war deterrent of the DPRK provided by Songun plays a decisive role in resolutely smashing the U.S. imperialists' moves to provoke a nuclear war on the Korean Peninsula and defending peace of the country and the security of the nation.

Energy Developed under Long-term Plan
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 5 (KCNA) -- Energy is being developed under a long-term plan in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 Kim Kyong Bong, director of the Natural Energy Development and Utilization Center under the State Academy of Sciences, told KCNA that the energy development has been conducted in a far-sighted way according to the actual conditions, and its vista is bright. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Successes are being made in researches into and the work of prospecting more energy resources rich in the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A nation-wide effort has been bent to making best use of hydraulic power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In recent years, dams of the Samsu Power Station and Nyongwon Power Station have been built and large hydro-power stations are under construction in various parts of the country, the prospect of which is also good. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Brisk is the construction of minor power stations are built in Jongphyong and Yonsa Counties and other areas with streams. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Priority is being given to geological prospecting and tunneling for securing more coal fields, so as to decisively ease the strain on power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Solar hothouses built in institutions, industrial establishments and rural areas are paying off. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Bio-methane has found its way to rural dwelling houses in the Migok Co-op Farm in Sariwon City, North Hwanghae Province and other areas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Wind-driven generators of various capacities are being manufactured and introduced to houses in rural and mountainous areas and efforts are being exerted to make an effective use of low-calorie coal and fly-ash. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, scientific research has been pushed ahead to widely use natural energies including solar, biological and tidal powers.

Preparations for Kimjongilia Festival Progress Apace
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 5 (KCNA) -- Preparations for the 11th Kimjongilia Festival to mark the February holiday (the birthday of Kim Jong Il) are going ahead in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 In an interview with KCNA, Ri Yong Je, a department director of the Korean Kimilsungia and Kimjongilia Committee, said: Festival preparations are being made in different parts of the country. The committee set the dawn of the great, prosperous and powerful nation glowing like the red color of Kimjongilia, the immortal flower, as the festival theme and is directing efforts to arranging the festival venue to suit the theme so as to attach greater significance to it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The floor of the central hall was renovated and decorations were made. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Festival posters are being created at final stage. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A meeting for exchanging experiences in the cultivation of the immortal flower will be held on the sidelines of the festival in line with the enthusiasm of the people to bring the flower into bloom more beautifully. New scientific and technological issues solved and experiences made in the cultivation of the flower will be published in various forms at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The number of applicants has considerably increased than ever before among domestic institutions, overseas Koreans and foreign organizations and individuals. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kimjongilias are opening flowers at Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia hothouses of ministries and national institutions including the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries and the Ministry of Finance and in different parts of the country.

Bell in Yonbok Temple
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 5 (KCNA) -- The bell in Yonbok Temple is one of the three famous bells in the DPRK along with the bells in Sangwon and Pongdok Temples. The bell, a national treasure, shows the then high standard of metal casting and metal craft technique of the Korean nation.
 It was cast in 1346 to suspend in Yonbok Temple in Kaesong, the capital of Koryo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When the temple was burned down in 1563, it was moved to Nam Gate in the crossroad in Pukan-dong, Kaesong City (today). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is 1.9 meters in diameter at its mouth, 3.12 meters high and 23 centimeters thick. It weighs some 14 tons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It shows a new aspect of bell in the period of Koryo in its form and decoration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bell-hook reflects two tangled dragons. They look like wriggling as if they were alive. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A row of lines was engraved at its waist dividing the upper from the lower part. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its mouth is hemmed with illustrations of waves and various animals such as dragons, deer, tortoises and crabs moving with the waves. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The decorations on the surface of the bell are refined, elegant and solemn and its beautiful and clean sound reverberates as far as 40 kilometers.
